<page_title>Changes of van der Waals forces do not affect speed distributions</page_title>
<text>Changes of van der Waals forces do not affect speed distributions
    
  
 
This computer experiment shows that Maxwell&apos;s theorem, which didn&apos;t originally consider interatomic interactions, can be applied to interacting atoms. The speed distributions seem to be solely determined by the masses of the atoms and the temperature --- you can tell this from the above simulation that the two types of atoms that apparently have different sizes have almost identical shape of distribution function.
Can you explain why?

</text>
